Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} on to boil for the potatoes.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer). Halve any thick
@Tenderstem® Broccoli{150%grams} stems lengthways.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @Echalion Shallot{1}. Peel and grate the
@Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

When your pan of water is boiling, add the potato chunks and cook until you can
easily slip a #knife{} through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the broccoli onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{},
season with @salt and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Set aside for now.

If you'd prefer to, boil your broccoli with the potatoes for the last ~{3-5%minutes}
of boiling time until tender, ~{3-5%minutes}. Remove from the potatoes before
mashing. Season with @salt and @ground black pepper{}.

Meanwhile, pop the @breadcrumbs{25%grams}, @Lemon & Herb Seasoning{1%sachet} and
@olive oil{1%tbsp} into a #small bowl{} and mix together.

Lay the @basa fillets{2} onto a lined baking tray.

Spoon the herb crumb evenly over the fish, pressing it down with the back of the
#spoon{}.

Pop the basa on the top shelf and the broccoli on the middle shelf of your oven
to cook until the veg is tender and the fish is cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked when opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a medium #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the shallot and stir-fry until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the
garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @cider vinegar{15%ml} and allow it to evaporate, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Pour in the @water{100%ml} and @vegetable stock paste{10%grams}, then bring to the
boil and simmer until reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes}. Vigorously stir in the
@butter{30%grams} until melted, then take off the heat.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off
the heat. Add a knob of @?butter{} and a splash of @?milk{} and mash with a
#potato masher{} until smooth. Season to taste with @salt and @ground black
pepper{}.

Serve the herb crusted basa with the mash and roasted broccoli alongside, then
spoon over the buttery sauce to finish. Enjoy!